<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-08-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="402" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d402">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Chargé <persName type="to">Sleeper</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-08-31"><hi rend="italic">August 31,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 59.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 160, of the 25th instant, reporting further in regard to the
                            insurrection in Cuba.</p>
                        <p>The department approves without reservation the energetic activity and
                            wise foresight displayed in your recent communication to the <pb facs="0570" n="464" xml:id="pg_464"/> Cuban Government. The
                            department desires you to call the attention of the Cuban Government to
                            any and every injury to American interests in Cuba and to urge the
                            Government to accord that protection without which American interests
                            must be jeopardized.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>